scene.message:
Kumi's Father: Club{nl}
activities this late? Kumi,{nl}
just what do you go to{nl}
school{waitkey}{clearbox}for, anyway? To study? Or to{nl}
fool around?{waitkey}{ret}

Kumi's Father: Your mother{nl}
told me. You had a test in{nl}
the 70s recently, didn't you.{waitkey}{clearbox}You get marks that low because{nl}
all you do is play instead of{nl}
study.{waitkey}{ret}

Kumi's Father: Your father{nl}
cuts back on the drink and{nl}
tobacco he loves, even gives{nl}
up weekend golf,{waitkey}{clearbox}to work and earn money — and{nl}
who do you think it's all{nl}
for?!{waitkey}{clearbox}It's to support you and your{nl}
mother, isn't it?{waitkey}{clearbox}Kumi, the only reason you can{nl}
attend school now is because{nl}
your father sweats and toils.{waitkey}{ret}

Kumi's Father: And yet you,{nl}
without a thought for your{nl}
father's hardships, neglect{nl}
your studies and{waitkey}fritter your time away on{nl}
clubs and play.{waitkey}{clearbox}The one at fault, Kumi, is{nl}
you.{waitkey}{ret}
